Dialogue: 0,0:00:02.13,0:00:05.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Starswirl: The best elements\Nwithin us can spread light
Dialogue: 0,0:00:05.94,0:00:09.71,Default,,0,0,0,,and virtue and I know ponies\Nwho represent them all:
Dialogue: 0,0:00:10.21,0:00:17.08,Default,,0,0,0,,strength, bravery, healing,\Nbeauty, hope and sorcery.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:17.89,0:00:21.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Myself and these Pillars of\NEquestria were gathered together
Dialogue: 0,0:00:21.79,0:00:24.93,Default,,0,0,0,,by another to maintain\Nand share the light
Dialogue: 0,0:00:25.03,0:00:27.26,Default,,0,0,0,,of these powerful ideals.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:27.56,0:00:31.56,Default,,0,0,0,,But we soon came to believe the\Npony who brought us together,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:31.77,0:00:34.47,Default,,0,0,0,,only wanted that\Npower for himself.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:35.77,0:00:39.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Cast out and alone,\Nthis power-mad pony
Dialogue: 0,0:00:39.24,0:00:43.28,Default,,0,0,0,,turned to darkness to\Nsatisfy his thirst.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:43.38,0:00:46.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Transformed into\Na Pony of Shadows,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:46.15,0:00:50.59,Default,,0,0,0,,he returned for revenge, to\Nextinguish the Pillars' light
Dialogue: 0,0:00:50.79,0:00:53.26,Default,,0,0,0,,and rob the world of hope.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:53.56,0:00:58.13,Default,,0,0,0,,To stop him, the Pillars and I\Nmust make a grave sacrifice.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:58.93,0:01:03.13,Default,,0,0,0,,But we shall leave behind a\Nseed in hopes that one day
Dialogue: 0,0:01:03.23,0:01:07.17,Default,,0,0,0,,it will grow into a force to\Nstand against the darkness
Dialogue: 0,0:01:07.27,0:01:08.47,Default,,0,0,0,,for all time.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:08.77,0:01:14.24,Default,,0,0,0,,We must now face the fiend\Nwith the only plan we have.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:14.64,0:01:17.04,Default,,0,0,0,,"I only hope it will be enough."
Dialogue: 0,0:01:17.85,0:01:19.18,Default,,0,0,0,,That's the last entry.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:19.58,0:01:22.88,Default,,0,0,0,,And maybe Starswirl's final\Nwords before he vanished!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:02.46,0:02:05.26,Default,,0,0,0,,I've always wondered\Nwhat happened to Starswirl.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:05.96,0:02:08.63,Default,,0,0,0,,This is quite a\Ndiscovery, Sunburst.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:09.43,0:02:10.60,Default,,0,0,0,,So it's genuine?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:10.70,0:02:13.00,Default,,0,0,0,,You can verify that this\Njournal really belonged
Dialogue: 0,0:02:13.10,0:02:14.50,Default,,0,0,0,,to Starswirl the Bearded!?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:14.80,0:02:15.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Indeed.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:15.77,0:02:17.54,Default,,0,0,0,,From the looks of it,\Nthe last thing he wrote
Dialogue: 0,0:02:17.64,0:02:19.84,Default,,0,0,0,,before facing the\NPony of Shadows.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:20.74,0:02:25.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh, so, the Pony of\NShadows was really real?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:25.68,0:02:27.05,Default,,0,0,0,,It appears so.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:27.25,0:02:30.02,Default,,0,0,0,,We never met the other\NPillars and we were too young
Dialogue: 0,0:02:30.12,0:02:32.19,Default,,0,0,0,,to understand the\Ndanger they faced.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:32.29,0:02:33.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Hold on a second now!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:33.92,0:02:36.69,Default,,0,0,0,,All those legendary\Nponies were real too?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:36.79,0:02:39.89,Default,,0,0,0,,And they went off with Starswirl\Nto face the Pony of Shadows
Dialogue: 0,0:02:39.99,0:02:42.79,Default,,0,0,0,,and then none of them were\Never heard from again?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:43.20,0:02:45.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah-ha, yeah. Weren't\Nyou listening?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:46.50,0:02:48.47,Default,,0,0,0,,But what happened\Nto them all?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:48.57,0:02:50.04,Default,,0,0,0,,They must have\Ndefeated the villain,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.14,0:02:52.51,Default,,0,0,0,,since Equestria's still\Nfull of light and hope.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:52.81,0:02:55.14,Default,,0,0,0,,But how? And where\Ndid they go?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:55.44,0:02:57.54,Default,,0,0,0,,My Olde Ponish\Nis a bit rusty,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:57.85,0:03:00.25,Default,,0,0,0,,but I wonder if the answers\Ncan be found somewhere
Dialogue: 0,0:03:00.35,0:03:02.25,Default,,0,0,0,,within the pages\Nof this book.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:02.65,0:03:06.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, I just happen to be\Nan expert in Olde Ponish.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.22,0:03:08.82,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, I've practically\Nmemorized every ancient text
Dialogue: 0,0:03:08.92,0:03:10.65,Default,,0,0,0,,about Starswirl there is.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:10.96,0:03:12.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Seriously. All\Nof them.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.23,0:03:15.63,Default,,0,0,0,,We have fond memories\Nof our old teacher.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:15.73,0:03:17.66,Default,,0,0,0,,If you could discover\Nwhat happened to him,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:17.86,0:03:19.39,Default,,0,0,0,,we would be most grateful.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:20.97,0:03:23.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Solving a thousands-year-old\Nmystery could take forever!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.04,0:03:28.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Think of the research, the\Nre-reading, the re-re-reading.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.81,0:03:32.81,Default,,0,0,0,,You might find\Nyou need help.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.61,0:03:37.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Luckily, she's got a whole\Nbushel of helpers right here.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:37.42,0:03:38.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Totally!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:38.45,0:03:42.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh, how long will all this\Nresearch take, exactly?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:43.16,0:03:44.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's get this\Nback to my library.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:44.96,0:03:47.33,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sure we'll figure out\Nwhat happened in no time.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.80,0:03:57.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Figure it out yet, Twilight?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.24,0:04:01.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Wha-WHAT?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.58,0:04:02.78,Default,,0,0,0,,What did you figure out?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.18,0:04:04.48,Default,,0,0,0,,[gasp] You figured something out!?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:05.98,0:04:06.88,Default,,0,0,0,,What is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.38,0:04:08.48,Default,,0,0,0,,[sigh] Nothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.68,0:04:11.58,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, Starswirl was\Na genius, obviously,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.79,0:04:13.16,Default,,0,0,0,,but forget Olde Ponish.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.25,0:04:14.68,Default,,0,0,0,,There's parts where\Nhis hornwriting
Dialogue: 0,0:04:14.79,0:04:16.32,Default,,0,0,0,,is like another language!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.52,0:04:17.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Agh!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:17.72,0:04:21.69,Default,,0,0,0,,[groan] Twilight, we've been\Nstudyin' and referencin'
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.80,0:04:25.77,Default,,0,0,0,,and cross referencing for\Nthree days straight now.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.07,0:04:28.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Ugh. I haven't spent\Nthis much time reading
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.90,0:04:31.40,Default,,0,0,0,,since the last Daring\NDo book came out.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.61,0:04:33.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Perhaps it is time\Nto take a break.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.57,0:04:36.50,Default,,0,0,0,,This mystery is over a\Nthousand years old, after all.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.61,0:04:38.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Another day or two\Nwon't make a difference!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.35,0:04:40.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Two days!?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.58,0:04:42.05,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't want to\Nwaste two seconds.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.15,0:04:45.32,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm close to an answer.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.42,0:04:46.25,Default,,0,0,0,,I can feel it.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.45,0:04:51.05,Default,,0,0,0,,"Hearg sylfum se\NPonhenge," What's that?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.46,0:04:53.19,Default,,0,0,0,,The Temple of Ponhenge?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.39,0:04:54.49,Default,,0,0,0,,You can read that!?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.80,0:04:56.53,Default,,0,0,0,,The hornwriting's\Npretty sloppy,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.63,0:04:58.46,Default,,0,0,0,,but it's nowhere\Nnear as bad as mine.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.97,0:05:03.64,Default,,0,0,0,,"Toward dol grimlic\Nof fola firgenbeorg?"
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.54,0:05:07.24,Default,,0,0,0,,At the base of Foal Mountain...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.84,0:05:10.04,Default,,0,0,0,,"User endemest scield... "
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.34,0:05:12.71,Default,,0,0,0,,[gasp] Our last stand.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.96,0:05:14.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Spike: [yawn]
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.08,0:05:18.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, that sure sounds\Nlike a clue to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.86,0:05:30.66,Default,,0,0,0,,This is it.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.76,0:05:31.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Ponhenge.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.27,0:05:33.54,Default,,0,0,0,,I can't believe it.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.44,0:05:40.74,Default,,0,0,0,,I've never seen magical\Nrunes like these before.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.94,0:05:41.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Have you?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.98,0:05:42.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh uh.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.01,0:05:50.01,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't think anypony's seen\Nany of this for a long time.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.72,0:05:52.25,Default,,0,0,0,,[struggle] Woah!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.39,0:05:57.53,Default,,0,0,0,,It'd take a whole team of ponies\Nto clear away all this brush.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.53,0:06:01.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Even then, I'm not\Nsure we'd find out
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.00,0:06:04.44,Default,,0,0,0,,what happened here a\Nthousand years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.33,0:06:07.10,Default,,0,0,0,,[sigh] You're right.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:07.60,0:06:09.47,Default,,0,0,0,,I suppose it was a long shot.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.77,0:06:10.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Cheer up, Twilight.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.84,0:06:13.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Finding a whole set of ancient\Nruins is pretty impressive.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.27,0:06:16.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Maybe you could\Nwrite a paper on it!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.51,0:06:18.91,Default,,0,0,0,,I guess I hoped we'd get here\Nand the mystery would just
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.01,0:06:20.61,Default,,0,0,0,,magically be explained.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.62,0:06:25.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh, Twilight?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.63,0:06:34.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Starswirl..?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.96,0:06:37.16,Default,,0,0,0,,I-- I've wanted to\Nmeet you my whole life!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.36,0:06:39.13,Default,,0,0,0,,I can't believe\Nyou're here!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.40,0:06:43.90,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't think\Nhe is here.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.50,0:06:46.30,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't think any\Nof them are.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.02,0:07:05.22,Default,,0,0,0,,You summon me at your\Nperil, Starswirl.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:05.53,0:07:09.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Once I defeat all of you, this\Nrealm will embrace the darkness
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.13,0:07:12.36,Default,,0,0,0,,as I did so long ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.41,0:07:26.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Drawing me here will\Nonly make me stronger.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.85,0:07:29.25,Default,,0,0,0,,You will never defeat me!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.35,0:07:31.95,Default,,0,0,0,,We did not come\Nhere to defeat you.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.80,0:07:45.07,Default,,0,0,0,,What are you doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:45.67,0:07:48.37,Default,,0,0,0,,We came to contain you.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.20,0:07:52.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Aaaaahhh!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:03.75,0:08:06.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, you did ask for\Na magical explanation!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.99,0:08:15.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh, what just happened?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:16.36,0:08:18.79,Default,,0,0,0,,It looked like\NStarswirl cast a spell
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.90,0:08:20.90,Default,,0,0,0,,that banished the\NPony of Shadows.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.20,0:08:23.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Of course! Powerful\Nmagic like that
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.97,0:08:25.77,Default,,0,0,0,,would leave an impression\Non this place.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.07,0:08:29.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Bringing the book back here\Nlet us see what happened.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:29.34,0:08:30.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Which was what?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.98,0:08:33.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Starswirl and the rest of the\NPillars sacrificed themselves
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.98,0:08:35.45,Default,,0,0,0,,to save Equestria.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:37.45,0:08:40.65,Default,,0,0,0,,It's amazing to think one of the\Ngreatest mysteries of Equestria
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.75,0:08:43.49,Default,,0,0,0,,was solved with a musty old\Nbook from an antique shop.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.99,0:08:46.12,Default,,0,0,0,,But I wouldn't say\Nthe mystery's solved.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:46.23,0:08:49.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Starswirl's spell was one of the\Nmost powerful feats of magic
Dialogue: 0,0:08:49.16,0:08:50.63,Default,,0,0,0,,in all of history.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.83,0:08:53.93,Default,,0,0,0,,It'll take years of study\Nbefore we fully understand it.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.03,0:08:56.40,Default,,0,0,0,,I think I understand\NStarswirl's spell!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:58.77,0:09:01.14,Default,,0,0,0,,I know I've finished one of\NStarswirl's spells before
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.34,0:09:03.71,Default,,0,0,0,,but this one was on a\Nwhole different level!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.81,0:09:05.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Was it an explosion\Nof magical feedback?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.68,0:09:06.48,Default,,0,0,0,,An evocation?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:06.58,0:09:07.68,Default,,0,0,0,,A kind of incantation?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.78,0:09:10.12,Default,,0,0,0,,It's Starswirl, so the\Npossibilities are endless!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.82,0:09:12.42,Default,,0,0,0,,And once Starlight set\Nme on the right track
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.52,0:09:13.82,Default,,0,0,0,,with his crazy hornwriting--
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.92,0:09:15.55,Default,,0,0,0,,[snigger] I mean, he was a genius,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:15.66,0:09:17.53,Default,,0,0,0,,so I guess we can forgive\Na little messiness --
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.72,0:09:20.49,Default,,0,0,0,,I went through the journal\Nagain and it's amazing!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:21.09,0:09:24.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Twilight, darling, we\Nunderstand you're excited,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:24.97,0:09:26.24,Default,,0,0,0,,but that's all we understand.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.73,0:09:28.86,Default,,0,0,0,,What exactly is so amazing?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:29.07,0:09:31.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Only how Starswirl\Nand the other Pillars
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.10,0:09:33.20,Default,,0,0,0,,sent the Pony of\NShadows to limbo!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:33.51,0:09:34.88,Default,,0,0,0,,They did what now?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.34,0:09:41.01,Default,,0,0,0,,They used their magic to\Nopen a portal between worlds,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:41.11,0:09:43.94,Default,,0,0,0,,to limbo and pulled the\NPony of Shadows inside.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:44.89,0:09:46.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Darling, your diorama!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:46.92,0:09:47.75,Default,,0,0,0,,I made more.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.26,0:09:52.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Starswirl thought the only way\Nto trap the Pony of Shadows
Dialogue: 0,0:09:52.86,0:09:54.93,Default,,0,0,0,,in limbo was for the\NPillars to take him there.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.23,0:09:57.77,Default,,0,0,0,,So they got stuck too!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:58.27,0:10:01.20,Default,,0,0,0,,The Pony of Shadows must\Nhave been really awful
Dialogue: 0,0:10:01.30,0:10:02.73,Default,,0,0,0,,for them to do that.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:03.24,0:10:06.17,Default,,0,0,0,,I suppose being trapped for all\Ntime with a super-duper bad guy
Dialogue: 0,0:10:06.27,0:10:08.67,Default,,0,0,0,,in limbo might be OK if\Nyou were doing the limbo,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:09.08,0:10:10.21,Default,,0,0,0,,but that's still pushing it.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:10.41,0:10:13.38,Default,,0,0,0,,The thing is, I think\NI can get them out.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:14.38,0:10:16.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Twilight, are you serious?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.18,0:10:19.78,Default,,0,0,0,,You can save the most\Nlegendary ponies of all time?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:19.89,0:10:20.99,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know..
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.19,0:10:25.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Opening portals between worlds\Ndidn't work out well for me.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:25.86,0:10:27.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you sure it's safe?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.49,0:10:30.22,Default,,0,0,0,,First of all, you opened\Nportals through time.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.33,0:10:32.40,Default,,0,0,0,,And second of all,\NStarswirl wrote the spell
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.50,0:10:33.30,Default,,0,0,0,,you used to do it.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:33.50,0:10:35.43,Default,,0,0,0,,If he'd been here, he\Ncould have stopped it.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:36.14,0:10:38.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Equestria would be\Nsafer with him in it.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:38.51,0:10:39.78,Default,,0,0,0,,We have to save him.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:40.17,0:10:43.11,Default,,0,0,0,,But you'd be savin'\Nall the Pillars, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:43.41,0:10:45.31,Default,,0,0,0,,And they disappeared\Nages ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.91,0:10:47.34,Default,,0,0,0,,That's the thing\Nabout limbo.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:47.45,0:10:49.15,Default,,0,0,0,,It isn't one\Nplace or another.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:49.25,0:10:51.78,Default,,0,0,0,,It's in between, so\Ntime stands still.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.89,0:10:54.36,Default,,0,0,0,,If we can pull them out, it'll\Nbe like they never left!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:54.56,0:10:56.73,Default,,0,0,0,,I actually built another\Nmodel to demonstrate--
Dialogue: 0,0:10:56.82,0:10:57.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Agh!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:58.46,0:10:59.86,Default,,0,0,0,,What can we do to help?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:59.96,0:11:02.49,Default,,0,0,0,,If I'm right, we need to find\Nitems that are connected
Dialogue: 0,0:11:02.60,0:11:04.03,Default,,0,0,0,,to the Pillars in some way.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.13,0:11:07.10,Default,,0,0,0,,You mean, like, stuff\Nthat belonged to them?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:07.20,0:11:08.93,Default,,0,0,0,,How would we know\Nwhat to look for?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:09.24,0:11:10.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Or where?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:11.04,0:11:13.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Luckily, Starswirl\Ntook a lot of notes.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:14.71,0:11:17.54,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1} My compatriots are as varied{\i0}\N{\i1} as the realm itself{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:17.64,0:11:20.11,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1} and hail from every{\i0}\N{\i1} corner of our land,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:20.31,0:11:23.98,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1} bringing with them artifacts{\i0}\N{\i1} and talismans of great power.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:24.18,0:11:26.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Um, Twilight, what\Nare you doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:27.89,0:11:29.26,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm not doing anything!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:31.02,0:11:32.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Rockhoof's shovel!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:32.76,0:11:34.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Flash Magnus' shield!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:35.10,0:11:36.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Mistmane's flower!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.96,0:11:38.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Meadowbrook's mask!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:39.03,0:11:41.03,Default,,0,0,0,,And the blindfold\NSomnambula wore
Dialogue: 0,0:11:41.13,0:11:43.26,Default,,0,0,0,,when she faced\Nthat nasty sphinx!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.90,0:11:47.33,Default,,0,0,0,,I guess we don't need to figure\Nout who should get what!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:53.35,0:11:56.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Professor! It's a\NMighty Helm headpiece!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.28,0:11:58.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Maybe it belonged\Nto Rockhoof himself!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:59.25,0:12:01.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Legends don't wear helmets.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:01.49,0:12:04.32,Default,,0,0,0,,This belonged to a real pony.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:04.42,0:12:05.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Applejack: Oh, I\Ncan guarantee
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.03,0:12:08.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Rockhoof was as real\Nas you and me.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:10.70,0:12:14.77,Default,,0,0,0,,And I suppose that ravine was\Ndug with his trusty shovel
Dialogue: 0,0:12:14.87,0:12:17.70,Default,,0,0,0,,to save the village from\Nan erupting volcano.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:18.10,0:12:18.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Probably.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.37,0:12:22.21,Default,,0,0,0,,I love old legends\Nas much as anypony,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.41,0:12:25.58,Default,,0,0,0,,but a pony strong enough to save\Na village from rushing lava
Dialogue: 0,0:12:25.68,0:12:28.95,Default,,0,0,0,,with a shovel is... preposterous!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:41.56,0:12:44.10,Default,,0,0,0,,I can't believe\Nyou just did that...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:44.50,0:12:45.87,Default,,0,0,0,,You saved us!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:46.27,0:12:48.64,Default,,0,0,0,,I bet if you told\Nsomepony else the story,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:48.74,0:12:51.57,Default,,0,0,0,,it might sound...\N{\i1} preposterous{\i0}.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:58.38,0:13:01.95,Default,,0,0,0,,I suppose some\Nstories.. might be true.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:05.05,0:13:07.99,Default,,0,0,0,,And Rockhoof's appears\Nto be one of them!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.86,0:13:19.86,Default,,0,0,0,,[slap]\NOW!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:19.93,0:13:22.80,Default,,0,0,0,,You keep those hooves\Nto yourself, dearie!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.20,0:13:26.64,Default,,0,0,0,,This place has been in my\Nfamily for generations
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.74,0:13:29.44,Default,,0,0,0,,and I'm not about to\Nlet some whippersnapper
Dialogue: 0,0:13:29.54,0:13:31.84,Default,,0,0,0,,take the last good\Npiece of it!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:32.15,0:13:36.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Time was, ponies came from far\Nand wide to see these gardens.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:36.98,0:13:40.48,Default,,0,0,0,,But that flower's the only\Nworthwhile thing left!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:57.80,0:14:00.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Perhaps it just seemed like\Nyour gardens were worthless,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:00.94,0:14:03.41,Default,,0,0,0,,but a little pruning\Ncan work wonders.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:04.41,0:14:05.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Of course you will\Nhave to look after
Dialogue: 0,0:14:05.88,0:14:07.75,Default,,0,0,0,,more than just\None flower now.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:08.55,0:14:12.32,Default,,0,0,0,,You've given me back\Nmy family's legacy.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:13.12,0:14:16.99,Default,,0,0,0,,The flower you wanted seems\Nlike a fair trade for that.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:20.73,0:14:23.16,Default,,0,0,0,,I can't believe Flash\NMagnus' shield
Dialogue: 0,0:14:23.26,0:14:25.29,Default,,0,0,0,,ended up in the Dragon Lands.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:26.00,0:14:28.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Good thing you brought the\NOfficial Equestrian Friendship
Dialogue: 0,0:14:28.44,0:14:31.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Ambassador To The Dragons to\Nhelp you navigate our customs.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:31.77,0:14:34.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Like our favorite\Nsport: gorge surfing!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:34.77,0:14:41.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Whoo hoo! HA HA AH AH!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:44.68,0:14:48.02,Default,,0,0,0,,OK. That was\Nawesome!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:48.92,0:14:52.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Dragon Lord Ember commanded\Nus to make peace with ponies,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:52.73,0:14:55.57,Default,,0,0,0,,but it doesn't mean you\Ncan surf in our spot.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:57.00,0:14:58.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Whoa! Fellas.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:58.70,0:15:00.70,Default,,0,0,0,,As the Official Equestrian\NFriendship Ambassador
Dialogue: 0,0:15:00.80,0:15:04.10,Default,,0,0,0,,To The Dragons, I have to say,\Nthat's not very friendly.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:04.50,0:15:06.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Garble: Well, what do\Nyou know?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:06.64,0:15:11.21,Default,,0,0,0,,The puny, pony dragon's\Nsticking up for his pony pal.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:12.68,0:15:15.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey! That's an ancient\Npony artifact.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:16.22,0:15:17.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Hooves off my gorge board!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:17.95,0:15:21.19,Default,,0,0,0,,I found it in the desert\Nand finders keepers.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:21.49,0:15:23.52,Default,,0,0,0,,It isn't yours.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:23.72,0:15:25.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh. It sure looks like mine.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:25.83,0:15:29.23,Default,,0,0,0,,But, I might consider\Nracing you for it.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:29.83,0:15:30.96,Default,,0,0,0,,No problem.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:31.56,0:15:33.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Um, no.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:33.13,0:15:34.83,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean.. you.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:36.04,0:15:36.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Heh heh.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:47.31,0:15:48.51,Default,,0,0,0,,On your marks...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:48.72,0:15:49.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Get set...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:49.88,0:15:50.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Surf!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:04.90,0:16:08.67,Default,,0,0,0,,[pants] I won? I won! WOOO-HOOO!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.77,0:16:10.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Give up the shield, Garble.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:11.84,0:16:15.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Lord Ember only commanded\Nus to be nice to ponies.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:15.51,0:16:20.28,Default,,0,0,0,,She never said anything\Nabout pony-loving dragons.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:24.18,0:16:27.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh.. since Dragon Lord Ember\Ncommanded you
Dialogue: 0,0:16:27.32,0:16:29.72,Default,,0,0,0,,to make peace with ponies,\Nyou can't very well
Dialogue: 0,0:16:29.82,0:16:32.29,Default,,0,0,0,,attack one of their\Nfriends, can you?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:33.96,0:16:35.36,Default,,0,0,0,,I guess we'll find out!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:41.30,0:16:44.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Ugh. Why is he always\Nhiding behind ponies?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:45.17,0:16:47.60,Default,,0,0,0,,I wasn't hiding when I\Nbeat you down the ridge.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:48.31,0:16:49.31,Default,,0,0,0,,You fell.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:49.81,0:16:53.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Wow, you must be slow, if\Nall Spike had to do to win
Dialogue: 0,0:16:53.35,0:16:54.72,Default,,0,0,0,,was fall down.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:55.02,0:16:56.35,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm faster than you.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:56.55,0:16:57.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Doubt it.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:57.38,0:16:57.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:58.19,0:16:59.79,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll race you back to the top.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:59.89,0:17:02.39,Default,,0,0,0,,If you win, you can\Nhave your pony junk.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:02.99,0:17:07.36,Default,,0,0,0,,But if I win, you'll leave\Nand I get to give it to him!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:07.66,0:17:10.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Fine. I'm pretty sure I\Ncould beat you anyway,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:10.90,0:17:13.53,Default,,0,0,0,,but with that heavy hunk\Nof metal on your back,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.73,0:17:15.30,Default,,0,0,0,,it'll be a snap.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:15.60,0:17:17.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh? Oh, yeah.\NThanks for the tip.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:18.84,0:17:20.57,Default,,0,0,0,,See ya at the top, loser!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:26.35,0:17:28.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey! That's mine!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:28.88,0:17:31.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Finders keepers, remember?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:32.42,0:17:34.62,Default,,0,0,0,,See, because that's\Nwhat you said to them
Dialogue: 0,0:17:34.72,0:17:36.09,Default,,0,0,0,,when they first\Nshowed up and--
Dialogue: 0,0:17:43.86,0:17:47.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Just remember not to\Nturn away from them, Cattail.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:47.10,0:17:49.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Flash bees can get\Npretty aggressive.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:49.84,0:17:51.81,Default,,0,0,0,,I guess that's why none of\Nthe other bayou animals
Dialogue: 0,0:17:51.91,0:17:52.98,Default,,0,0,0,,can get to the water.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:54.54,0:17:57.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Wouldn't it make more sense\Nfor you to wear the mask
Dialogue: 0,0:17:57.14,0:17:58.27,Default,,0,0,0,,that calms the bees?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:58.68,0:18:03.62,Default,,0,0,0,,It would... if I didn't have to\Nfly up here to move their hive.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:05.52,0:18:06.19,Default,,0,0,0,,There!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:10.86,0:18:12.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Now the other bayou creatures\Ncan get to the water
Dialogue: 0,0:18:12.89,0:18:14.79,Default,,0,0,0,,without the bees\Nfeeling threatened.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:16.10,0:18:18.54,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, you didn't\Nhave to help with this.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:18.73,0:18:21.06,Default,,0,0,0,,I would've lent you\Nthe mask anyway.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:21.27,0:18:22.74,Default,,0,0,0,,I know. [giggle]
Dialogue: 0,0:18:22.84,0:18:24.54,Default,,0,0,0,,But I couldn't leave\Nwithout helping.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:26.77,0:18:29.47,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't think anypony can\Nfind anything in there.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:30.08,0:18:32.25,Default,,0,0,0,,I wouldn't give\Nup hope just yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:38.82,0:18:41.09,Default,,0,0,0,,This old blindfold was\Nstuck in the drain.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:41.49,0:18:43.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Weren't you looking\Nfor a blindfold?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:43.52,0:18:44.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, yeah!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:49.19,0:18:51.86,Default,,0,0,0,,I can't believe I'm going to\Nmeet Starswirl the Bearded,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:52.17,0:18:53.80,Default,,0,0,0,,you know, outside of my dreams..
Dialogue: 0,0:18:53.90,0:18:56.23,Default,,0,0,0,,I can't believe you're actually\Ngoing through with it.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:56.64,0:18:57.44,Default,,0,0,0,,What do you mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:58.34,0:19:00.64,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm all for pushing the\Nenvelope, obviously,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:00.84,0:19:03.21,Default,,0,0,0,,but this is pretty out\Nthere for you, Twilight.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:03.81,0:19:06.51,Default,,0,0,0,,What's "out there" about saving\Nthe most legendary ponies
Dialogue: 0,0:19:06.61,0:19:09.58,Default,,0,0,0,,of all time from a\Nthousands year-old prison?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:09.98,0:19:12.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, nothing when\Nyou say it like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:13.35,0:19:16.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Unless "the most legendary\Nponies of all time"
Dialogue: 0,0:19:16.19,0:19:19.06,Default,,0,0,0,,knew what they were doing and\Nwe shouldn't mess with it.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:19.66,0:19:22.63,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sure Starswirl and the\NPillars did the best they could
Dialogue: 0,0:19:22.73,0:19:25.93,Default,,0,0,0,,back then, but magic\Nhas come a long way,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:26.13,0:19:28.33,Default,,0,0,0,,mostly because of\Nthe work they did.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:28.74,0:19:30.74,Default,,0,0,0,,That's true. And you\Ndid get your wings
Dialogue: 0,0:19:30.84,0:19:32.84,Default,,0,0,0,,from finishing one of\NStarswirl's spells.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:33.84,0:19:34.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Exactly.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:35.94,0:19:40.04,Default,,0,0,0,,But, then I messed with one and\Nnearly destroyed the universe,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:40.15,0:19:41.12,Default,,0,0,0,,so...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:41.31,0:19:44.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Starlight, Starswirl the\NBearded is the greatest wizard
Dialogue: 0,0:19:44.18,0:19:45.15,Default,,0,0,0,,who ever lived.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:45.45,0:19:48.68,Default,,0,0,0,,The chance to have him back in\NEquestria is worth the risk.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:48.79,0:19:49.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Spike: That's good news.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:50.39,0:19:53.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Otherwise, we'd have brought\Nthis shield for nothing!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:54.03,0:19:55.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Applejack: I hope you don't\Nthink you're the only one
Dialogue: 0,0:19:55.96,0:20:00.03,Default,,0,0,0,,to find her artifact, because\Nthis here shovel says otherwise.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:00.43,0:20:02.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Honestly, you two...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:02.70,0:20:04.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Not everything is a competition.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:04.87,0:20:07.40,Default,,0,0,0,,But.. Mistmane's\Nflower is by far
Dialogue: 0,0:20:07.51,0:20:09.21,Default,,0,0,0,,the most attractive\Nof the artifacts.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:09.61,0:20:11.74,Default,,0,0,0,,You're just saying that because\Nyou didn't have to scuba dive
Dialogue: 0,0:20:11.85,0:20:14.32,Default,,0,0,0,,in a pit of green\Nslime to get yours.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:14.71,0:20:16.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Or move a Flash Bee hive.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:17.28,0:20:18.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Good work everyone.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:20.39,0:20:21.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's do this!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:43.68,0:20:45.91,Default,,0,0,0,,What-- What has happened?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:46.71,0:20:49.08,Default,,0,0,0,,It worked! We brought you back!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:49.28,0:20:50.41,Default,,0,0,0,,To where?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:50.52,0:20:52.25,Default,,0,0,0,,You and the others have\Nbeen trapped in limbo
Dialogue: 0,0:20:52.35,0:20:53.78,Default,,0,0,0,,for over a thousand years,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:53.99,0:20:55.72,Default,,0,0,0,,but I figured out\Nhow to get you ho--
Dialogue: 0,0:20:55.82,0:20:56.69,Default,,0,0,0,,What!?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:56.79,0:21:00.26,Default,,0,0,0,,No, no, no, no! You must\Nundo what you've done!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:00.56,0:21:01.76,Default,,0,0,0,,What? Why?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:01.96,0:21:03.86,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, I don't\Nthink I can.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:04.16,0:21:06.26,Default,,0,0,0,,You cannot\Nbring us back!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:06.47,0:21:07.27,Default,,0,0,0,,But I did.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:07.37,0:21:09.04,Default,,0,0,0,,I brought all the Pillars back.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:09.24,0:21:12.41,Default,,0,0,0,,You cannot bring only\Nthe Pillars back...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:28.32,0:21:29.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, no...
